#Graphic session: log out -> log in as new user (upper right corner).

# SSH: Go to VirtualBox setting for Debian -> Network -> advanced settings -> Port forwarding
# -> fill in the info
#(e.g. Youtube tutorial https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ErzhbUusgdI for Guest port, Host port).
# Find IP of Host (in my case Windows laptop -> ipconfig)
# Find IP of Guest (Debian running on the same laptop -> ip addr)
# Use the host computer command line to sign in using SSH
# syntax: ssh -p [Host port] [username in Debian(preceeding @-sign)]@[my Windows IP]
# e.g. ssh -p 3022 testuser@[my IP on my Windows laptop in the network]
# exit to end session